  <description><![CDATA[<p>Villa La Gardenia &amp; Oleandra is a real hidden gem in <a data-udi="umb://document/604dbba59ac64320ab6e9f1e89231a4c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/604dbba59ac64320ab6e9f1e89231a4c}" title="Limone">Limone</a>. It’s located above the town so you get fantastic views of the lake– you could sit in the garden admiring the lake and mountain scenery all day.</p>
<h2>A tranquil getaway on the lake</h2>
<p>There are three villas making up the hotel; each surrounded by palm and olive trees. The pool and sun terrace are the best places to relax and top up your tan. The restaurant also takes advantage of the views with a terrace overlooking the lake. This hotel is perfect if you're looking for somewhere very peaceful and a bit out of the way. It's been done up to a very high quality, and as a result has people coming back year on year.</p>
<h2>Private paths and guided walks</h2>
<p>The centre of Limone isn't far away, but far enough that the hotel feels like it's own private oasis. Take your time wandering around the old cobbled streets and boutique shops in the old town and if you can, join the hotel owners on their weekly guided walk – it’s a great way to get to know Limone better. There's even a private path that leads straight from the hotel to a waterfall and an incredible panoramic view-point. The walk takes about an hour but there are places to stop and rest along the way.</p>]]></description>
